About Me



Hi, I am a final year student pursuing MSc. Computer Science from Department of Computer Science, University of Delhi.
I love to code and solve algorithmic challenges. I am also interested in Machine Learning and Deep Learning.
If you are interested, you can view some of my favorite projects in my portfolio down below.

Projects

Buffer Cache Simulation

A simulation of Buffer Cache Management System in Multiprogramming Environment. Implemented getblk and brelse algorithms of the operating system that handle the buffers used by processes.

University of Delhi Scorecard Fetcher

A web-scraping system that emails the candidate his/her scorecard upon the declaration of result. The system is capable of fetching scorecards of different colleges and courses throughout Delhi University.

Driver Drowsiness Detection System

A computer vision system that detects driver drowsiness in a real-time video stream. An alarm is triggered if the driver appears to be drowsy depending upon the driver failing a certain threshold score. The system can also be deployed to prevent/detect fatigue-related accidents.

AI Image Captioning Bot

A Deep Learning model for Image Captioning, wherein the bot takes an image from the user and generates captions describing it. For easy access, the system is deployed as a Flask Web Application The model uses transfer learning to extract features from an image which are further used by LSTM layers to generate captions.
